WEBVTT

00:00:00.910 --> 00:00:04.309
Satan is the main peace-recker.

00:00:04.309 --> 00:00:08.230
The scriptures tell us that he is driven by great anger.

00:00:08.230 --> 00:00:12.429
His anger is malicious and uncontrolled.

00:00:12.429 --> 00:00:19.030
Would any sound-minded God-fearing person allow himself to reflect Satan's vicious anger?

00:00:19.030 --> 00:00:20.589
Of course not.

00:00:20.589 --> 00:00:27.429
That is why all true servants of God are determined to put away uncontrolled anger.

00:00:27.629 --> 00:00:32.229
But apart from uncontrolled anger, is all anger bad?

00:00:32.229 --> 00:00:35.469
The Bible does not condemn all anger.

00:00:35.469 --> 00:00:41.109
It teaches us that anger is wrong when it is uncontrolled or unjustified.

00:00:41.109 --> 00:00:48.149
At Ephesians 4.26, God's Word tells us to be wrathful, but it adds do not sin.

00:00:48.149 --> 00:00:54.710
At times, anger may simply be a strong feeling that comes into us because of being upset or annoyed

00:00:54.710 --> 00:00:58.509
by something that we see as being wrong.

00:00:58.509 --> 00:01:01.590
That in itself is not bad.

00:01:01.590 --> 00:01:06.129
But what makes anger bad is when it fills a person's heart.

00:01:06.129 --> 00:01:09.349
And here she just loses control of it.

00:01:09.349 --> 00:01:15.750
When that happens, it may cause a person to act without a sound mind.

00:01:15.750 --> 00:01:20.750
Those who continue to lash out an anger will not gain salvation.

00:01:20.750 --> 00:01:26.950
Ephesians 5.20 lists fits of anger among the works of the flesh that will prevent a person

00:01:26.950 --> 00:01:29.469
from inheriting God's kingdom.

00:01:29.469 --> 00:01:33.750
There will be no place for such ones in God's new world.

00:01:33.750 --> 00:01:39.530
A brief review of how uncontrolled anger wrecks peace for ourselves and others will highlight

00:01:39.530 --> 00:01:42.670
why this is so.

00:01:42.670 --> 00:01:48.230
Uncontrolled anger harms both the angry person as well as those around him.

00:01:48.230 --> 00:01:55.549
We read at Proverbs 29-22 that an angry person stirs up strife, adding that he commits

00:01:55.549 --> 00:01:58.390
many transgressions.

00:01:58.390 --> 00:02:01.989
One of these many sins is abusive speech.

00:02:01.989 --> 00:02:08.370
We must work to show restraint when speaking with workmates, with strangers in the ministry,

00:02:08.370 --> 00:02:14.270
with our brothers and sisters in the congregation, and with our family members.

00:02:14.270 --> 00:02:18.110
Bad feelings must be controlled.

00:02:18.110 --> 00:02:23.629
A speech ridicule, contempt, and hateful anger are wrong.

00:02:23.629 --> 00:02:29.949
Giving vent to such feelings can destroy precious friendships with other people and with

00:02:29.949 --> 00:02:31.830
Jehovah.

00:02:31.830 --> 00:02:33.550
Don't be like a volcano.

00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:36.069
That will not quiet down.

00:02:36.069 --> 00:02:40.669
Just like an erupting volcano will harm those living around it.

00:02:40.669 --> 00:02:46.949
So too a person who expresses intense anger will harm those living around him.

00:02:46.949 --> 00:02:56.389
He also damages himself in what way, acting on anger often leads to even more aggression.

00:02:56.389 --> 00:03:00.629
So then uncontrolled anger can also affect our own peace.

00:03:00.629 --> 00:03:04.270
It can cause us to do something that we will later regret.

00:03:04.270 --> 00:03:07.789
It can have a negative effect on our health.

00:03:07.789 --> 00:03:13.469
Medical studies show that uncontrolled anger can cause high blood pressure and respiratory

00:03:13.469 --> 00:03:14.469
problems.

00:03:14.469 --> 00:03:21.110
It can also affect the liver and pancreas, and such anger can cause digestive problems.

00:03:21.110 --> 00:03:26.469
When a person becomes angry, he or she will not always think clearly.

00:03:26.469 --> 00:03:30.990
After a fit of rage, a person may become depressed.

00:03:30.990 --> 00:03:39.750
No wonder we read at Proverbs 14 and verse 30 that a calm heart gives life to the body.

00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:45.710
The disastrous consequences of uncontrolled anger are illustrated in God's word by

00:03:45.710 --> 00:03:51.870
the actions of Simeon and Levi, sons of the patriarch Jacob.

00:03:51.870 --> 00:03:57.150
When they learned that their sister Dino was violated by a man named Sheikam, we read

00:03:57.150 --> 00:04:03.990
a Genesis 34 and verse 7 that they were offended and very angry.

00:04:03.990 --> 00:04:09.110
Now they had a valid reason to be angry, but they took their anger too far.

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:11.310
It was uncontrolled.

00:04:11.310 --> 00:04:14.990
Simeon and Levi took vengeance on Sheikam.

00:04:14.990 --> 00:04:21.069
Using deception, they attacked and killed every male in Sheikam city.

00:04:21.069 --> 00:04:26.470
Then along with the other sons of Jacob, they plundered it and took the women and little

00:04:26.470 --> 00:04:29.110
children captive.

00:04:29.110 --> 00:04:36.189
Dino's tragic experience must have grieved Jacob greatly, yet he condemned his son's

00:04:36.189 --> 00:04:38.870
uncontrolled anger.

00:04:38.870 --> 00:04:44.350
Simeon and Levi tried to justify their actions, but that was not the end of the matter because

00:04:44.350 --> 00:04:47.629
Jehovah was also displeased.

00:04:47.629 --> 00:04:53.709
For this reason, Jacob later foretold that the descendants of Simeon and Levi were to

00:04:53.709 --> 00:04:58.189
be scattered among the tribes of Israel.

00:04:58.189 --> 00:05:05.350
Their uncontrolled anger brought disfavor from God and from their father Jacob.

00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:11.589
Otherwise, to pay attention to such scriptural accounts and put away uncontrolled anger

00:05:11.589 --> 00:05:14.870
and all of the harm that it brings.

