00:07:48.639 --> 00:07:54.079
If so, you know what uncontrolled anger can lead to.

00:07:54.079 --> 00:07:57.680
Now that we've defined uncontrolled anger

00:07:57.680 --> 00:08:00.360
and considered what it can lead to,

00:08:00.360 --> 00:08:02.360
the next question is,

00:08:02.360 --> 00:08:06.680
how can we put away uncontrolled anger?

00:08:06.680 --> 00:08:11.319
First, we need to recognize the danger of uncontrolled anger.

00:08:11.319 --> 00:08:14.040
Proverbs 25-28 states

00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:17.519
that as a city broken through, without a wall,

00:08:17.519 --> 00:08:21.800
is the man who cannot control his temper.

00:08:21.800 --> 00:08:25.480
Strong city walls were vital in ancient times.

00:08:25.480 --> 00:08:28.600
Without them, a city would quickly fall to invaders,

00:08:28.600 --> 00:08:29.600
likewise.

00:08:29.600 --> 00:08:33.080
So will those who cannot control their temper.

00:08:33.080 --> 00:08:34.759
By losing control,

00:08:34.759 --> 00:08:39.879
they make themselves vulnerable to the invasion of wrong thoughts,

00:08:39.879 --> 00:08:44.080
thoughts that can cause them to hurt themselves, and others.

00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:48.240
Uncontrolled anger can do just that.

00:08:48.240 --> 00:08:51.159
Next, after recognizing the danger,

00:08:51.159 --> 00:08:54.720
we must pause and then deal with the anger

00:08:54.720 --> 00:08:58.960
before it causes us to do something that we will regret.

00:08:58.960 --> 00:09:00.440
When anger grows within us,

00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:04.720
we're wise to recall what happened with Simeon and Levi.

00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:06.639
We might also recall what happened

00:09:06.639 --> 00:09:10.559
in the video dramatization that we just viewed.

00:09:10.559 --> 00:09:12.720
You see, in each case,

00:09:12.720 --> 00:09:15.679
pausing before reacting out of anger

00:09:15.679 --> 00:09:18.000
may have spared much pain and heartache.

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:19.399
True?

00:09:19.399 --> 00:09:24.200
That is why we have this warning at Proverbs 17 and verse 14.

00:09:24.200 --> 00:09:29.159
Before the quarrel breaks out, take your leave.

00:09:29.159 --> 00:09:32.159
With that in mind, each of us should ask himself,

00:09:32.159 --> 00:09:34.559
do I tend to jump to conclusions

00:09:34.559 --> 00:09:37.080
when I don't have all the facts?

00:09:37.080 --> 00:09:40.879
If so, can I take my leave and put away anger

00:09:40.879 --> 00:09:43.960
before it starts to build up?

00:09:43.960 --> 00:09:48.240
The inspired advice found that James chapter 1 and verse 19

00:09:48.240 --> 00:09:49.799
will help us to do so.

00:09:49.799 --> 00:09:53.960
But only if we make a sincere and determined effort

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.480
to apply what it says.

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:58.000
Let's read that verse.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:01.559
James chapter 1 and verse 19.

00:10:01.559 --> 00:10:03.799
And here we find some simple steps

00:10:03.799 --> 00:10:08.000
to help us put away uncontrolled anger.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:10.840
It says, no this, my beloved brothers.

00:10:10.840 --> 00:10:15.200
Everyone must be quick to listen, slow to speak,

00:10:15.200 --> 00:10:17.159
slow to anger.

00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:22.039
If we ask Jehovah to help us with this,

00:10:22.039 --> 00:10:25.639
namely to be quick to listen, slow to speak,

00:10:25.639 --> 00:10:29.240
slow to anger, he will assist us to do so.

00:10:29.240 --> 00:10:32.200
He will help us to see the facts of a matter,

00:10:32.200 --> 00:10:38.080
show understanding, and then put away uncontrolled anger.

00:10:38.080 --> 00:10:43.000
A word of caution, though, to succeed in doing our part,

00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:47.120
we must choose our associates wisely.

00:10:47.120 --> 00:10:49.840
We could undermine all of our good work

00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:53.440
and Jehovah's help in controlling our anger

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:56.639
if we choose associates who are arrogant,

00:10:56.639 --> 00:11:01.639
opinionated, or quick to become angry.

00:11:01.679 --> 00:11:04.759
Regarding someone who is disposed to rage,

00:11:04.759 --> 00:11:08.480
Proverbs chapter 22 verse 25 warns,

00:11:08.480 --> 00:11:10.759
never learn his ways.

00:11:11.919 --> 00:11:14.960
Well, we've enjoyed another outstanding series of talks

00:11:14.960 --> 00:11:19.320
that should help us to keep awake, maintain fine conduct,

00:11:19.320 --> 00:11:23.679
and escape the judgment that will soon come in on this world.

00:11:23.679 --> 00:11:26.279
As this symposium has emphasized,

00:11:26.279 --> 00:11:30.360
we must do our utmost to continue to put away peace records

00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:35.120
such as inappropriate boasting, envy, dishonesty,

00:11:35.120 --> 00:11:39.360
harmful gossip, and uncontrolled anger.

00:11:39.360 --> 00:11:42.720
If we have a problem with any of the peacemaking qualities

00:11:42.720 --> 00:11:45.279
that we have discussed in this symposium,

00:11:45.279 --> 00:11:50.279
seek Jehovah's hope to change and then work at it.

00:11:50.440 --> 00:11:54.240
Our sincere efforts to pursue peace with our brothers

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:57.799
and our sisters will influence how earnestly

00:11:57.840 --> 00:12:02.600
we are awaiting Jehovah's Day and his promised new world.

00:12:02.600 --> 00:12:06.240
Yes, our genuine efforts will affect our hearts

00:12:06.240 --> 00:12:09.639
and will be noticed by our Heavenly Father.

00:12:09.639 --> 00:12:12.879
Then, in his great mercy,

00:12:12.879 --> 00:12:16.720
Jehovah will consider us to be, as his word says,

00:12:16.720 --> 00:12:20.960
spotless and unblemished and in peace,

00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:24.600
both with him and with our fellow worshipers.
